nowFeed.headline: The Jets interviewed Panthers OC Joe Brady for their head-coaching vacancy, the team said. No doubt, Brady has a promising future, but he's only 31 and has only one year of coordinator/position-coach experience on the NFL level. This would be a bold, outside-the-box hire for the Jets. There are more qualified candidates than Brady; this would be a risky bet on potential.

nowFeed.headline: Sal Paolantonio reports that Washington Football Team quarterback Alex Smith will arrive at FedEx Field later this afternoon between 4:30 & 5 PM. Smith will be evaluated by the team's medical staff and then Head Coach Ron Rivera will make a determination about Smith‘s status for tonight‘s game against the Buccaneers. Smith told Paolantonio this week that he is determined to play, but the WFT is prepared to start Taylor Heinicke should Smith be deemed unable to go.

nowFeed.headline: Bobby Wagner was voted an Associated Press First Team All-Pro for the sixth time in his career and fifth straight year. Per the AP, Wagner is the 11th linebacker since AP started the All-Pro team in the 1940s to make the first team at least six times. The other 10 are in the Pro Football Hall of Fame. Receiver DK Metcalf and safety Jamal Adams were voted to the AP All-Pro second team. Punter Michael Dickson, special teamer  Nick Bellore and long-snapper Tyler Ott also received All-Pro votes.

nowFeed.headline: Guard Brandon Scherff was named first team All-Pro by the Associated Press -- the first time a Washington player has earned such an honor since punter Matt Turk in 1996. Scherff is Washington's first lineman to be named to this team since tackle Jim Lachey in 1991. Scherff is a pending free agent after playing this season on the franchise tag. Coach Ron Rivera has praised him often this season, both for his play and his leadership. Scherff isn't a big talker, but sets a good tone with his work.

nowFeed.headline:
Dolphins CB Xavien Howard and K Jason Sanders both voted AP 1st team all-pro for the first time in their career.

Howard was the NFL's interception leader with 10, and first player with double-digit interceptions in 13 seasons. He received 47 of 50 votes, easily most among CBs.

Sanders made more 50+ FGs than anyone else with strong accuracy all year. He received 23 of 50 votes, most among all kickers.

nowFeed.headline: Jake Bailey (punter) and Gunner Olszewski (punt returner) have earned Associated Press All-Pro honors, an impressive feat that generally carries more meaning that Pro Bowl berths because of the limited spots. Bailey's 45.6 yard net is the second best in NFL history. Olszewski's punt return average (17.3) is the second best in the NFL since 1970 (minimum of 20 returns).
